- *India has accelerated* its semiconductor progress, achieving in two years what took the US and China over a decade.
- Industry leaders and global companies see *India as a strategic hub*, with increased exhibition participation and $16-18 billion in new projects.
- Experts emphasize the importance of *ecosystem depth*, talent, and policy support to sustain this rapid growth and turn manufacturing into innovation.

